[Thanks to Jacques Morvan for this additional information. I apologize for
not having posted this message sooner but I had been attempting to obtain,
for posting, whatever information my sources in Madagascar might be able to
provide regarding West Nile virus infection of lemurs. Not having received a
reply to my message, I can only conclude that I do not have sources in
Madagascar. Also, this series is named somewhat incorrectly. The virus is
West Nile virus. The fever it can cause is West Nile fever. It is incorrect
to say "West Nile fever virus", but I have continued this titling to keep
from confusing those who might do a TOPICS search. I have been trying to get
the world to do things my way for >60 years but have not yet been successful.
I will simply have to try harder. -- Mod CHC
